{{Infobox Figure Skating Competition |title= 2010 Austrian Figure Skating Championships |image= |imagesize= |caption= |comptype= National Championships |startdate= 10 December |enddate= 12 December |skatingseason= 2009-2010 |location= [[Innsbruck]] |host= |venue= [[Tiroler Wasserkraftarena]] |prizemoney= |championmen= [[Viktor Pfeifer]] |championladies= [[Miriam Ziegler]] |championdance= [[Kira Geil]] / [[Dmytri Matsjuk]] |previouscomp= [[2009 Austrian Figure Skating Championships]] |nextcomp= [[2011 Austrian Figure Skating Championships]] }} The '''2010 Austrian Figure Skating Championships''' ({{lang-de| Österreichischen Staatsmeisterschaften im Eiskunstlauf 2010}}) were the [[Austrian Figure Skating Championships]] of the 2009-2010 [[figure skating season]]. Skaters competed in the disciplines of [[single skating|men's singles, ladies singles]], and [[ice dancing]] on the senior level for the title of [[list of national championships in figure skating|national champion]] of [[Austria]]. The results of the national championships were used to choose the Austrian teams to the [[2010 World Figure Skating Championships]] and the [[2010 European Figure Skating Championships]].
The 2010 Championships took place between 10 December and 12 December 2009 in the [[Tiroler Wasserkraftarena]] in [[Innsbruck]]. The Junior-level Championships were held immediately prior to the Senior-level championships in the same location and arena, between 8 December and 10 December. The senior [[compulsory dance]] was the Tango Romantica and the junior was the Westminster Waltz.
