{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Coast Gymkhana Club Ground | nickname = | country = Kenya | image = | location = [[Mombasa]], [[Kenya]] | establishment = 1999 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 2010 | club1 = [[Kenya national cricket team|Kenya]] | date = 18 October | year = 2011 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/16/5532.html Ground profile }}
'''Coast Gymkhana Club Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Mombasa]], [[Kenya]]. The first recorded match held on the ground came in 1999 when a Coast Cricket Association XI played the touring [[Marylebone Cricket Club]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/16/5532_misc.html|title=Other matches played on Coast Gymkhana Club Ground|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=18 October 2011}}</ref> The ground held its first [[List A cricket|List A]] match in 2010 when [[Kenya national cricket team|Kenya]] played the [[United Arab Emirates national cricket team|United Arab Emirates]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/16/5532_a.html|title=List A Matches played on Coast Gymkhana Club Ground|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=18 October 2011}}</ref> Kenya won the match by 24 runs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/307/307873.html|title=Kenya v United Arab Emirates, 2010|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=18 October 2011}}</ref>
The ground is owned by the Coast Gymkhana Club. The club is located roughly a hundred metres from the [[Mombasa Sports Club]], which has hosted [[One Day International]]s.
