{{Infobox_Stadium | stadium_name = Denizli Atatürk Stadium | nickname = | image = [[File:Denizli Atatürk Stadyumu.jpg|center|250px|]] | location = [[Denizli]], [[Turkey]]| broke_ground = | opened = 1950 | renovation = 1987 | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Denizlispor]] | operator = | surface = Grass | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = | seating_capacity = 15,427<ref name="ws" /> | tenants = | }} '''Denizli Atatürk Stadium''' ({{lang-tr|Denizli Atatürk Stadyumu}}) is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Denizli]], [[Turkey]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is the home ground of [[Denizlispor]]. The stadium holds 15,427 people and was built in 1950.<ref name="ws">[http://www.tff.org.tr/Default.aspx?pageID=394&stadID=55 TFF: Denizli Atatürk Stadi]</ref>
