{{Infobox sportsperson | headercolor = lightblue | name = Romain Marchessou | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birth_name = | fullname = | nickname = | nationality = {{MON}} | residence = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1985|9|9|df=yes}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | height = {{height|m=1.75|abbr=on}} | weight = {{convert|77|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}} | website = | country = | sport = [[Olympic weightlifting|Weightlifting]] | event = 77 kg | collegeteam = | club = | team = | turnedpro = | coach = | retired = | coaching = | worlds = | regionals = | nationals = | olympics = | paralympics = | highestranking = | pb = | medaltemplates = }}
'''Romain Marchessou''' (born September 9, 1985) is a Monegasque [[weightlifter]].<ref>{{cite sports-reference|Romain Marchessou|https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ma/romain-marchessou-1.html|28 January 2013}}</ref> Marchessou represented [[Monaco]] at the [[2008 Summer Olympics]] in [[Beijing]], where he competed for the [[Weightlifting at the 2008 Summer Olympics – Men's 77 kg|men's middleweight category]] (77&nbsp;kg). Marchessou placed twenty-fourth in this event, as he successfully lifted 110&nbsp;kg in the single-motion [[snatch (weightlifting)|snatch]], and hoisted 140&nbsp;kg in the two-part, shoulder-to-overhead [[clean and jerk]], for a total of 250&nbsp;kg.<ref>{{cite news|title=Men's 77kg (170 lbs)|url=http://www.2008.nbcolympics.com/weightlifting/resultsandschedules/rsc=WLM077000/standings.html|publisher=[[NBC Olympics]]|accessdate=28 January 2013}}</ref>
