{{Infobox NRHP | name = Sylvan Hills Country Club Golf Course | nrhp_type = | image = Sylvan Hills Country Club Golf Course.JPG | caption = | location = Intersection of Club and Country Club Roads, [[Sherwood, Arkansas]] | coordinates = {{coord|34|49|19|N|92|13|48|W|region:US-AR_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = Arkansas | built = {{Start date|1927}} | architect = [[Justin Matthews]] | architecture = [[Recreation]], | added = {{Date|2010|04|16}} | sigdate1_label = Operated as "North Hills Country Club" | sigdate1 = 1956 to May 2007 | sigdate2_label = Closed for Operation | sigdate2 = May 2007 | area = {{convert|120|acre|ha}} | mpsub = Arkansas Highway History and Architecture, 1910-1965 | refnum = 10000289<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|2010a}}</ref> }}
'''The Greens at North Hills Municipal Golf Course''' is a municipal [[golf course]] located in [[Sherwood, Arkansas]], [[United States]]. Construction of the {{convert|120|acre|ha}} golf course began in 1927 during the "golden era" of golf course design.
Originally named the '''Sylvan Hills Country Club Golf Course''' and developed by the [[Justin Matthews]] Co., the course was added to the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 2010 due to its local significance and association with entertainment and recreation,<ref name="ahpp">{{cite web |url=http://www.arkansaspreservation.com/historic-properties/_search_nomination_popup.aspx?id=2544 |title=Sylvan Hills Country Club Golf Course, Sherwood, Pulaski County |publisher=Arkansas Historic Preservation Program |accessdate=May 26, 2013}}</ref> From 1956 through May 2007, the golf course was named the '''North Hills Country Club'''.<ref name="ahc">{{cite web |url=http://www.encyclopediaofarkansas.net/encyclopedia/entry-detail.aspx?entryID=7645 |title=Greens at North Hills, aka: Sylvan Hills Country Club Golf Course |publisher=Encyclopedia of Arkansas History & Culture |first1=Darrell W. |last1=Brown |date=May 10, 2013 |accessdate=May 26, 2013}}</ref>
