'''Valentyna Salamakha''' ([[Russian language|Russian]]: Valentyna Саламаха born 23 April 1986)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurohandball.com/ec/ehfc/men/2011-12/player/522015/ValentynaSalamakha|title=Valentyna Salamakha Profile|publisher=European Handball Federation|accessdate=30 November 2017}}</ref> is an [[Azerbaijan]]i professional [[handball]] goalkeeper who plays for [[SG BBM Bietigheim]].
==Career== Arriving from [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen (handball)|Bayer Leverkusen]], Salamakha signed a two-year contract with [[Siófok KC]] in 2015.<ref name=sio>{{cite web|url=http://siofokkc.hu/felnott/ukran-valogatott-kapussal-erosit-csapatunk-valentyna-salamakha-alairt|title=Válogatott kapussal erősít csapatunk- Valentyna Salamakha aláírt!|publisher=Siófok KC Official Website|date=23 April 2015|accessdate=30 November 2017|language=Hungarian}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.werkselfen.de/news/1255-valentyna-salamakha-wechselt-nach-ungarn|title=Valentyna Salamakha wechselt nach Ungarn|publisher=Bayer Leverkusen Official Website|date=23 April 2015|accessdate=30 November 2017|language=German}}</ref> Just after a season the Azerbaijani international moved back to Germany, signing to [[SG BBM Bietigheim]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sgbbm.de/aktuelles/top-torhueterin-fuer-die-sg-bbm-frauen.html|title=Top-Torhüterin für die SG BBM-Frauen|publisher=SG BBM Bietigheim Official Website|date=3 June 2016|accessdate=30 November 2017|language=German}}</ref>
