{{Orphan|date=December 2015}} {{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Xilingol Sports Center | nickname = | image = | fullname = | pushpin_map = China Inner Mongolia#China | pushpin_mapsize = | pushpin_map_caption = Location in Inner Mongolia | pushpin_label_position = | address = | location = [[Xilinhot]], [[Inner Mongolia]], [[China]] | coordinates = {{Coord|43.9323|116.0318|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 2013 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = | construction_cost = | architect = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor= | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | tenants = | seating_capacity = 25,685 | website = {{url|http://www.xlglty.com/}} }}
The '''Xilingol (Xilinguole) Sports Center''' ({{zh|s=锡林郭勒体育中心}}) is a sports venue in [[Xilinhot]], the capital of [[Xilingol League]], [[Inner Mongolia]], China. Built to host the 8th Inner Mongolia Minorities Games in August 2013, it has become a local landmark and has hosted many events including the 2017 Four-Country Women's Basketball Tournament, Asian Youth Wushu Tournament, and ''[[The Voice of China]]'' Xilingol finals. In 2015, the center was opened for use to the general public.<ref name=chinanews>{{cite news |url=http://www.nmg.chinanews.com/news/20170602/5416.html |title=内蒙古锡林郭勒体育中心场馆对外开放见成效 |work=China News |date=2 June 2017}}</ref>
The sports center consists of a [[multi-purpose stadium]] with a seating capacity of 25,685, six outdoor soccer pitches and two indoor ones, a basketball/ice hockey arena with 3,033 seats, a table tennis stadium with 30 tables and 662 seats, a wrestling stadium with 548 seats, a tennis stadium with four courts, a [[natatorium]] with an eight-lane swimming pool and diving platforms, a [[gateball]] stadium with three fields, and a badminton/archery stadium.<ref name=about>{{cite web |url=http://www.xlglty.com/zoujinchangguan/changguangaikuang/2016-04-27/3.html |title=Overview |publisher=Xilingol Sports Center |accessdate=2 September 2017}}</ref>
